headline: Bitcoin Price Falls Below $82,000, Crypto Stocks Slide After Tariff Plans
summary: Bitcoin sank Thursday as investors continued to flee riskier assets after President Trump ratcheted up the trade war.  The largest cryptocurrency recently traded around $82,000, down more than 4% from 24 hours ago, according to CoinDesk.

headline: US crypto stocks slide as Trump's sweeping tariffs jolt markets
summary: (Reuters) -     U.S. crypto stocks declined on Thursday after President Donald Trump's latest round of sweeping tariffs rattled investor confidence due to rising global trade tensions, sparking a sell-off in riskier assets.
